---
import SetupCard from '../ui/SetupCard.astro';
import { FileCode, Bot, GitMerge, ShieldCheck, Layers, Wrench } from '@lucide/astro';
---

<section id="ai" class="ai-section fade-up" aria-labelledby="ai-heading">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="section-intro">
      <h2 id="ai-heading">How I use AI</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        I use AI as a tool to augment my work, not as a shortcut. It's a teammate that can handle rote tasks and generate first drafts, but it doesn't replace the need for human judgment and creativity.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card-row card-row-3">

      <SetupCard title="The agent rules live in the repo" icon={Layers}>
        <p>Reuse existing components, create design tokens, enforce WCAG. <code>.github/copilot-instructions.md</code>
        and component APIs. The AI works within the system, not around it.</p>
      </SetupCard>

      <SetupCard title="Structured workflows" icon={GitMerge}>
        <p>Spec → generate → agent review → validate (typecheck, lint, tests,
        build) → human review. Same sequence every time. Predictable output is the point.</p>
      </SetupCard>

      <SetupCard title="PRDs before prompts" icon={FileCode}>
        <p>Every feature chunk starts with a written spec: scope, constraints, component
        reuse rules, acceptance criteria. The agent works from a document, not a vibe.</p>
      </SetupCard>

      <SetupCard title="Multiple agents, one task" icon={Bot}>
        <p>I run agents in parallel on different sub-tasks: one generating, one reviewing the
        contract, one checking accessibility. I treat them as a pipeline with distinct roles.</p>
      </SetupCard>

      <SetupCard title="AI reviews first, I review after" icon={ShieldCheck}>
        <p>Before I look at generated code, the agent reviews its own output against the spec. My
        pass is the senior-engineer layer: architecture, edge cases, things the agent can't "see".</p>
      </SetupCard>

      <SetupCard title="I pick the right tool for the task" icon={Wrench}>
        <p>Claude for planning and designing, ChatGPT for logic and debugging. I use Copilot Pro+ for model access so I'm always working with current frontier models.</p>
      </SetupCard>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .ai-section {
    padding-block: var(--space-16);
  }

  .section-intro {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-8);
  }

  .section-lead {
    color: var(--tone-text-muted);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.2vw, 1.15rem);
    max-width: 64ch;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .card-row {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .card-row-3 {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .card-row-3 {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 680px) {
    .card-row-3 {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
